{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/textandrandomness"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TextAndRandomness"},"abstract":[{"text":"Re-skin the engine’s stock lines, and roll dice that replay.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two systems give a game its voice: "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameText","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", the table of every stock line the engine can say, and the seeded random stream behind "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/random(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oneOf(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/chance(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which lets responses vary without ever varying between replays of the same seed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Speaking in your own voice","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Speaking-in-your-own-voice"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Every standard response — ","type":"text"},{"code":"Taken.","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"You can't go that way.","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the inventory header, the parser’s complaints — lives on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameText","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" value. Override any subset from your game’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" property; everything you don’t touch keeps the classic default:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct Snark: Game {","    \/\/ …","","    var text: GameText {","        var text = GameText()","        text.taken = \"Snagged.\"","        text.cantGoThatWay = \"Walls exist, you know.\"","        return text","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Fixed lines are plain strings. Lines built around a name are closures, so the override controls the whole sentence:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["text.cantReach = { \"The \\($0) is right there, and yet.\" }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The article helpers the defaults use — ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameText\/indefinite(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameText\/indefiniteList(_:)","isActive":true},{"text":" — are public statics, so custom lines can format listings the same way the engine does.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Text a game declares itself (descriptions, rule replies) never goes through ","type":"text"},{"code":"GameText","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; it’s already in your voice.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Randomness-that-replays","text":"Randomness that replays"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rule bodies can vary their behavior with three helpers:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["thief.before(.examine) {","    try reply(oneOf(","        \"The thief eyes you with polite menace.\",","        \"The thief pretends not to notice you.\",","    ))","}","","world.afterEachTurn {","    if chance(5) {","        say(\"Somewhere below, something skitters.\")","    }","}","","let damage = random(2...12)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three draw from one stream whose position lives in the world state. That buys two guarantees:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replays"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": a world built with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/init(game:seed:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" plays out identically for the same seed and commands, on every platform — the backbone of transcript tests and reproducible bug reports. The plain "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/init(game:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" seeds fresh each run."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Saves","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the stream’s position is part of the saved state, so a restored game continues with exactly the randomness it would have had."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pin the seed in a test the same way the engine’s own suite does:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let world = try GameWorld(game: MyGame(), seed: 42)"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"See-also","type":"heading","text":"See also"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Text-and-Randomness","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameText","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/random(_:)","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/chance(_:)"],"title":"Text and Randomness","generated":true}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Text and Randomness","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"